	<key>readme</key>
	<string>Search Swiss local weather forecasts from [MeteoSwiss](https://www.meteoswiss.admin.ch) by postal code or place name.

## Usage

Trigger with the keyword `weather` (configurable in the workflow's Configure panel) followed by:

- **A postal code** — `weather 8001` → Zürich, …
- **A place name** — `weather basel` → Basel (4001)

Press Enter on a result to open its local forecast in your browser. The place-name search is fuzzy and diacritic-insensitive (`zurich` matches `Zürich`).

## Setup

No dependencies — uses Python 3, which is pre-installed on macOS. Just import the workflow and go.

Source &amp; issues: https://github.com/maximehk/alfred-meteoswiss
</string>
